text: Richard Fitzgerald (1831–1884) was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross. Richard Fitzgerald may also refer to: *Richard B. Fitzgerald (c. 1843–1918), American businessman *Richard Fitzgerald (died 1776) (1733–1776), Irish Member of Parliament *Richard FitzGerald, 3rd Earl of Kildare *Richard Albert Fitzgerald (1806–1847), Irish Repeal Association politician *Richard Joseph Fitzgerald (1881–1956), bishop of Gibraltar *Rich Fitzgerald (born 1959), Pittsburgh politician and Allegheny County Executive *Richie Fitzgerald, Irish surfer *Dick Fitzgerald (Gaelic footballer) (1882–1930), Irish Gaelic football player *Dick Fitzgerald (Australian footballer) (1889–1957), Australian rules footballer *Dick Fitzgerald (basketball) (1920–1968), American basketball player
title: Richard Fitzgerald (disambiguation)
